        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 2:28PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 228 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sierraville, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sierraville, Calpine, and Sattley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
